description: This file defines data models used in the mobile app, including Book, Category, OrderModel, and WishlistEntry classes. These models are primarily used for representing and transferring data within the app related to books, categories, orders, and wishlist entries.

classes.name: Book
classes.description: Represents a book with properties like id, title, author, cover URL, description, price, rating, and category.

classes.name: Category
classes.description: Represents a category grouping for books with slug and name.

classes.name: OrderModel
classes.description: Represents a simplified order including id, book, quantity, status, and placement date.

classes.name: WishlistEntry
classes.description: Represents a wishlist item with id and associated book.

methods.name: copyWith
methods.description: Creates a copy of a Book object with optional updated fields.
